Yeah, I mean, scientists don’t just look at every problem and say, ‘Yeah we can totally fix that’ but rather, ‘We can fix that, but how exactly?’. I like characters who are scientists but not the ones who just happen to possess all-knowing knowledge like a cure for all cancers, disease, aging, my sleeping hours etc. IMO it’s going to get boring when there is this one science-leader is written the same way as the other science-leader-character-person.
